{"name":"Bone Commander - HD - Animated Doll","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/paralysis.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Make sure this classes level follows the chart below for HD.</p><p>At 1st level, the dollmaker summons the souls of the dead to inhabit animated dolls. These animated dolls function as the bone commander class feature, except for the fact they count as Construct and Undead, and gain the Construct traits in addition to their Undead traits.</p><p>The dollmaker begins play with a masterwork animated doll of any kind. These animated dolls use the bone commander advancement table, gaining skills, natural armor bonus, saves, feats, class features, and stat points based on their primary and secondary ability scores. These animated dolls cannot use any weapons or wear any magical items but can be enchanted like a normal animated doll. They also cannot push or pull stuff, or interact with anything (such as applying a healing potion to a person). When attacking, they use their Dexterity modifier plus their BAB to attack with, and their Charisma modifier for damage, but otherwise acts as the animated doll’s attack. Since spirits inhabit these animated dolls, they are always activated, only when the dollmaker is asleep or otherwise unconscious, do they become inanimate.</p><p>At 5th level and every four necromancer levels thereafter, the dollmaker can put another undead spirit into another animated doll. However, the dollmaker must have a masterwork or enhanced animated doll to put a spirit into. In addition, the dollmaker ignores the limitation of having only 1 animated doll out at a time.</p><p>Table: Bone Commander Base Statistics</p><table id=\"tablepress-49\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" aria-labelledby=\"tablepress-49-name\"><thead><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><p>Class<br>Level</p></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">HD</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">BAB</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">Fort</td><td st