d><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+11</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+9</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">60</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">19th</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">15</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+11</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+9</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">60</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\">20th</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">16</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+12</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">+10</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">64</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Class Level: The character’s necromancer level. The necromancer’s class levels stack with levels of any other classes that are entitled to a bone commander for the purpose of determining the bone commander’s statistics.</p><p>HD: This is the total number of eight-sided (d8) Hit Dice the bone commander possesses, but it possesses no Constitution score. Bone commanders use their Charisma score in place of their Constitution score.</p><p>BAB: This is the bone commander’s base attack bonus. Bone commanders do not gain additional attacks using their natural weapons for a high base attack bonus.</p><p>Fort/Ref/Will: These are the bone commander’s base saving throw bonuses. A bone commander has good Will saves.</p><p>Skills: This lists the total skill ranks for the bone commander. Bone commanders can assign skill ranks to any skill listed below. A bone commander cannot have more ranks in a skill than it has Hit Dice.</p><p>Bone commanders can have ranks in any of the following skills:</p><p>Acrobatics, Climb, Disguise, Intimidate, Knowledge (arcana), Knowledge (religion), Perception, Sense Motive, Spellcraft, Stealth, and Swim. In addition, at 1st level, the necromancer can choose 4 additional skills to be class skills for his bone commander.</p><p>Feats: This is the total number of feats possessed by a bone commander. Bone commanders can select any feat that they qualify for. Bone commander feats are set once chosen.</p>","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"lcnjxowa","formula":"floor(@classes.boneCommanderHd.level/3)","operator":"add","target":"","subTarget":"nac","modifier":"base","priority":0,"value":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"name":"Slam","uuid":"Compendium.ffd20-content.ffd20-class-pack-base_necromancer.Rdo6qYDkILUQxMcE","level":1},{"name":"Phantasmal Strings (Su)","uuid":"Compendium.ffd20-content.ffd20-class-pack-base_necromancer.iq4Q3mo3xy3DfMUk","level":1},{"name":"Limit Break: Forbidden Grimoire (Su)","uuid":"Compendium.ffd20-content.ffd20-class-pack-base_necromancer.6WISaEpcJ76MLMhz","level":1}]},"tag":"boneCommanderHd","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":["lgt","med","hvy","shl"],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":["sim","mar"],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{}},"scriptCalls":[],"subType":"racial","classSubType":"baseArc","parentClass":"Necromancer","level":2,"lvl":0,"hd":8,"hp":8,"classCastingStat":"noncaster","classBaseMPTypes":"noncaster","classBaseMPauto":"yes","mp":0,"bab":"med","skillsPerLevel":4,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"low"},"ref":{"value":"low"},"will":{"value":"high"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"blf":false,"clm":true,"crf":false,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":true,"dri":false,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":false,"int":true,"kar":true,"kdu":false,"ken":false,"kge":false,"khi"