{"name":"Erudite Casting","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<h3 id=\"erudite-casting\"><strong>Erudite Casting</strong></h3><p>Instead of being merely obsessive, the dollmaker’s abilities come from research and understanding, his necromancer class features now use his Intelligence instead of his Charisma modifier, and his spellcasting is based on Intelligence.</p><ul><li><strong>Bonus Spells: </strong>The dollmaker gains <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/m/mending/\">Mending </a>and <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/a/alter-object/\">Alter Object </a>as cantrips, and these spells at their respective levels: <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/c/crafters-knowledge/\">Crafter’s Knowledge </a>– 3rd, <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/m/make-whole/\">Make Whole </a>– 5th, <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/w/wind-back-the-key/\">Wind Back the Key </a>– 7th, <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/m/make-whole-greater/\">Make Whole, Greater </a>– 9th, <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/p/pasts-facade/\">Past’s Facade </a>– 11th, <a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/magic/spells/a/animate-objects/\">Animate Objects </a>– 13th.</li><li><strong>Limited Necromancy: </strong>The dollmaker is not a full necromancer. And as thus his ability to manipulate undead is less substantial to a true necromancer, The dollmaker can only maintain undead up to twice his necromancer level (his animated dolls are exempt from this).</li></ul><p>This ability alters the necromancer’s spellcasting, cantrips, and class features.</p><hr><p><a href=\"https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/base-classes/necromancer/archetypes/dollmaker/#erudite-casting\">Link to Ability on FFd20 </a>This version updated on 02/18/2024</p>","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"actions":[],"uses":{"per":"","value":0,"maxFormula":"","autoDeductCharg